<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211 Laredo/32: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Governor of Texas</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moody</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-06">January 6, 1930</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your wire January 4th is clear and to the point and greatly strengthens
                            our position with Mexico.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>